Here are five grant opportunities for biochemists researching cancer biology:

1. **Research Scholar Grants (RSG)**
   - **Funding Organization:** American Cancer Society (ACS)
   - **Funding Amount:** Up to $215,000 per year (direct costs) for up to 4 years, plus 10% allowable indirect costs
   - **Eligibility Criteria:** Independent investigators within the first 10 years of their initial faculty appointment; applicants should not hold more than one R01 or R01-equivalent grant at the time of application
   - **Link to Application Information:** https://www.cancer.org/research/we-fund-cancer-research/apply-research-grant/grant-types/research-scholar-grants.html
   - **Application Deadline:** June 1, 2025

2. **NCI Small Grants Program for Cancer Research (R03)**
   - **Funding Organization:** National Cancer Institute (NCI)
   - **Funding Amount:** Up to $50,000 per year (direct costs) for up to 2 years
   - **Eligibility Criteria:** Researchers at institutions eligible to receive NIH grants; open to both new and established investigators proposing small, self-contained research projects
   - **Link to Application Information:** https://grants.nih.gov/grants/guide/pa-files/PAR-23-058.html
   - **Application Deadlines:** Multiple dates in 2025, including February 24, June 20, and October 17

3. **AACR Research Fellowships**
   - **Funding Organization:** American Association for Cancer Research (AACR)
   - **Funding Amount:** Typically $50,000 to $120,000 over 1 to 2 years (amounts and durations may vary)
   - **Eligibility Criteria:** Postdoctoral and clinical research fellows working in cancer research; specific eligibility may vary by fellowship
   - **Link to Application Information:** https://www.aacr.org/professionals/research-funding/funding-opportunities-under-development/
   - **Application Deadline:** Specific deadlines for 2025 to be announced; refer to AACR's website for updates

4. **Institutional Research Grants (IRG)**
   - **Funding Organization:** American Cancer Society (ACS)
   - **Funding Amount:** Average of $120,000 per year, awarded to institutions as block grants
   - **Eligibility Criteria:** Institutions apply for grants to provide seed money to junior faculty for cancer research projects; individual eligibility determined by the institution
   - **Link to Application Information:** https://www.cancer.org/research/we-fund-cancer-research/apply-research-grant/grant-types/institutional-research-grants.html
   - **Application Deadline:** June 1, 2025

5. **Pilot Project Awards**
   - **Funding Organization:** Case Comprehensive Cancer Center
   - **Funding Amount:** $60,000 to $180,000, depending on the specific award
   - **Eligibility Criteria:** Faculty members at Case Western Reserve University and affiliated institutions; focus on innovative cancer research projects
   - **Link to Application Information:** https://case.edu/cancer/research/funding-opportunities
   - **Application Deadlines:** January 15, 2025, for most pilot awards

